body:
I have this problem on Mac OS X 10.11.6, too. Neither the current master 7f936eaa379e88869fcdb187d084f9bd7300c792 nor the v1.0.0 tag works with the `./greeter_server` example.

The same code totally works on Ubuntu 16.04.1 LTS, though.

@amerry Could you please provide more information about your workaround? Thanks!

I've re-opened the issue - we should verify before closing.
@Toldy can you provide more details of your installation? Is this from brew or manually, also which version of gRPC are you using?
Per @sab24's comment can you confirm if this is due to older versions of libgrpc in your system?

These seem to be different issues.
@athei The problem is caused by the version number of protobuf. We've removed those generated files in #8380.
@sab24 The problem seems to be caused by #8680. We are working on a fix for it.
